# React Component Patterns

## Component Structure

```tsx
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from 'react'
import type { Player } from '@retrofoot/core/types'

// 2. Props interface
interface PlayerCardProps {
  player: Player
  onSelect?: (id: string) => void
}

// 3. Component (hooks → handlers → render)
export function PlayerCard({ player, onSelect }: PlayerCardProps) {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false)

  function handleClick() {
    onSelect?.(player.id)
  }

  return <div onClick={handleClick}>{player.name}</div>
}
```

## Rules

- Function components only (no classes)
- Named exports (no default exports)
- Hooks at top, before logic
- Early returns for loading/error states

## State Management

- Local UI state: `useState`
- Global app state: Zustand stores in `lib/store.ts`

## Styling (Tailwind)

- Dark theme: `bg-slate-900`, `bg-slate-800`, `border-slate-700`
- Accent: `text-pitch-400`, `border-pitch-500`
- Retro font: `font-pixel` (Press Start 2P)
